The paper discusses a protocol for millimeter-wave cellular communications that minimizes the impact on human health. This involves considerations of information theory (cs.IT) to achieve maximum data rate, network infrastructure (cs.NI) for cellular communications, millimeter-wave technology (cs.MM), electromagnetic fields (cs.EM), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) for the impact on human health.
